70.4	Ophthalmology	Ophthalmology	Ophthalmology is the branch of medicine that deals with the anatomy, physiology and diseases of the eye. An ophthalmologist is a specialist in medical and surgical eye problems. Since ophthalmologists perform operations on eyes, they are considered to be both surgical and medical specialists.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Geraet_beim_Optiker.jpg/250px-Geraet_beim_Optiker.jpg
